  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Governing requirement: FDA-CPB-REQ-001 mandates that the computational hemolysis model demonstrate sufficient credibility at MRL 2 prior to submission. An inline requirement object capturing this mandate is documented within the package evidence record; however, the formal bindsRequirement linkage at the UnitOfAssurance level is not present in this profile binding.",
